title: Appointments to Human Organ Transplant Board
content_text: The appointments will take effect from February 15. Details are as follows: Re-appointment of substantive members --------------------------------------------- Miss Sandy Wong Hang-yee (Chairperson) Dr Mark Li Kin-yin (Vice-Chairperson) Ms Samantha Ko Kit-mui Dr Raymond Lo See-kit Ms Priscilla Wong Wai-yee Re-appointment of panel members --------------------------------------------- Dr Chan Kwok-ki Miss Louisa Chu Wai-san Dr Joan Fok Pui-chu Mr Jason Joseph Lee Kwong-yee Mr Jonathan Lee Wing-fung Dr Grace Lui Chung-yan Dr Joyce Tang Shao-fen Serving substantive member Dr Chan

Dr Grace Lui Chung-yan Dr Joyce Tang Shao-fen Serving substantive member Dr Chan Ka-lai will retire from the Human Organ Transplant Board upon completion of her term on February 14. A spokesman for the Food and Health Bureau expressed appreciation for the service and contribution of Dr Chan to the Board. Established under section 3 of the Human Organ Transplant Ordinance (Cap. 465), the Board is tasked to consider applications made for the Board's written approval to carry out restricted organ removals and/or restricted organ transplants, to receive prescribed information about transplant operations and certificates accompanying imported organs, and to perform any other

to receive prescribed information about transplant operations and certificates accompanying imported organs, and to perform any other functions that the Board is required or permitted to perform under the Ordinance.
